Hey buddy, I am going to rant a bit, but absolutely in your favor. I follow you as the primary current source of Star Wars information, but I have never commented before. Before you, I relied on Ain't it Cool News and The Force.net for my SW info. Before that there were some message boards going back for me as far as 1995 (I didn't know how to use a computer before that). I am not sure how old you are, but while I am not ancient, I think I have a few years on you. The first Star Wars movie I remember seeing in the theater was Return of the Jedi, I was too young to remember the other two. Thankfully, I do remember being around at the beginning of home video and that is when I remember seeing all of them. I also grew up without a TV, but we did have a monitor and VCR and the Star Wars series was among the few movies that I was allowed to watch whenever I wanted to. I even recorded the original trilogy on cassette tape and listed to them on road trips.

Here is a history trip that I bet nobody remembers. Back in the late 70's or early 80's my brother had a book written about Star Wars that compared it to the bible. Obi-Wan was compared to Jesus, and Darth Vader to the devil. I don't remember much of the details, or what my brother ever did with that book, but I know he had it at least until the early 90's and I would get a kick out of reading that today.

Anyways, my point is, I don't think you are a shill. My kids became SW fans too, each to different degrees. We were at lunch today talking about the current movie, but we all agreed that we enjoyed it. Sure, each of us had some little criticisms, but we also found how it fit perfectly into the overall story. When I watch your videos, I see someone like myself and my kids. I think you watch the movies with hope and an open mind and all you are looking for is to enjoy the ride. That is what I want and why I have enjoyed every SW movie (Even Solo).

For those of you haters, I bet you would have help ruin the original trilogy. If the internet was a big deal in the late 70's into the 80's you would have pointed out all the flaws. Yes, I recognize that there are flaws in the OT. The ride was fantastic though. George experimented in the prequel trilogy and some things worked, while some didn't. So what. Go try to make multiple billion dollar blockbusters yourself. I know I couldn't do it, and I am sure you can't either. I am glad that GL tried his best for 6 movies. Then he decided that rather than to kill his stories, he would give up his control while giving the stories a chance to live on. Without that decision we would not have The Mandalorian which I completely enjoy. Without George's decision, we would not have as many great minds taking a shot at expanding the story.


To the claims of you being a Disney shill during this holiday season, I say Bah, humbug. Keep being a fan and sharing all that you do. SW is so much fun and I am glad that there is still so much more about this universe that I will get to enjoy in my life. Keep being the fan that you are and I will keep watching.

snippet.textDisplay:
If you are a shill, can you get Disney to fund your fan-films? They would make a good feature length film!
Jokes aside, yeah, nah. You're not a shill. I came out of the movie happy. Sure the plot and story are contrived and mediocre at best, but I felt that is was because they were trying to make 3 films in one. Had it been put over two or three movies, it would not have been rushed and the contrivances would have been unnecessary.
I have my issues with it, but the film at least felt like an attempt to return to the Star Wars I knew before TFA, and tried to fix issues the fans had. We got Rey training and failing (although not much), we got backstory/development for Finn and Poe, we got some (albeit bad) story for Snoke, we got a backtrack from most of TLJ, we even got Reylo (sorta), and I finally got something I had been looking forward to since I first saw RotJ...Jedi Master Leia. These things should have come in TFA and TLJ, but sadly they did not. The point is that it was at least fun for me. The best of the saga? No, not by a mile. Best of the sequels? Yes for me.
Much like RotS, it suffers from, and had to fix, what came before.
And if you think it is too contrived or confused to be a good/fun movie, then try half of the stories fans got in Legends/EU. Some of the points are ripped straight from those stories. And some stories, such as all the Luke clones, are horrid.
Put bluntly, although the story is contrived, the fans were given things we wanted (or at least what I wanted) since TFA. The real issues are that Episode 9 had to retcon the issues in 7 and 8, there was no consistent story (or writer) for 3 movies, it was very rushed, and it was made as part of a sequel trilogy to a completed story. Ever since the sequel trilogy was announced, I feared it would fail because anything after RotJ will be compared to Eps IV-VI. Star Wars faces the same issue as Terminator and Alien...nothing compares to T2 or Aliens, and thus new films will always fall short.

SPOILERS AHEAD!


I get your point... it is an enjoyable film and its got its moments... mostly for me the ones that worked best were the OT ones such as Luke finally lifting his x-wing to Jhon Williams score, Lando speaking about how they were not alone and had each other to survive the difficult times and Leia`s final dissapearing... "letting go" only after Kylo was redeemed (an amazing moment... a mother´s moment!)... Ian Mcdiarmind was a delight again as the emperor... (do you notice a OT pattern there?)


However... as a WHOLE, this trilogy was a failure... and it is totaly disney's fault. It is very hard to believe that for an IP this big, they did not even have a plan! why in the world they let RJ do anything he wanted with TLJ just to erase everything after? (I didn`t like TLJ btw, even though its got the most beautiful explanation of the force I`d seen in a SW movie, I am just emphasizing they did not had a plan)... why after realizing they needed help they ask advice from George Lucas only to send his ideas away a second time? for crying out loud!


Just ask yourself this honestly: did you care about ANY of the new characters the way you did for Luke, Leia, Han, Lando, Obi Wan or Anakin? I DID NOT! I could not care less about any of them dying... and how come that rey is now a Skywalker??? she should have continued as Rey Palpatine, proving that your actions define you and not your name!!


THIS SAGA NEEDED GEORGE LUCAS. and this come from someone who was not a big fan of the prequels (loved revenge of the sith, but TPM and AOTC not too much), and who does not consider him the best director in the world, but he knows THE HEART OF THE STORY...


I guess i will stick to the EU..., considering 1 - 6 as the only canon!
